      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(outbound): materialize buffer-only message.send attachments",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhat problem does this PR solve?\n\n- `message.send` could fail when callers supplied attachment bytes only via `buffer` + `filename` + `contentType`, because the durable send path expected `media`/`mediaUrl` paths and never materialized buffer-only payloads.\n\nWhy does this matter now?\n\n- Issue [#90768](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/90768): in-memory artifact delivery workflows hit a dead end unless callers manually staged a local file first (`impact:message-loss`).\n\nWhat is the intended outcome?\n\n- Buffer-only `send` params are staged into the OpenClaw outbound media store and exposed as `media`/`mediaUrl`/`mediaUrls` before normal channel delivery, preserving the existing URL/path contract and the default outbound media byte cap.\n\nWhat is intentionally out of scope?\n\n- No per-channel buffer contracts, LM Studio/plugin changes, or `sendAttachment` behavior changes; explicit `media`/`mediaUrl`/`path` sources are left untouched.\n\nWhat does success look like?\n\n- `message.send` with only `buffer` + metadata delivers through `executeSendAction` with a staged outbound media path; oversized buffer-only payloads are rejected before staging; buffer-only params without explicit media sources no longer fail the send assembly path.\n\nWhat should reviewers focus on?\n\n- `resolveSendBufferMaxBytes` + `materializeSendBufferMediaParams` in `message-action-params.ts` (uses `MEDIA_MAX_BYTES`, not an unbounded fallback)\n- `resolveOutboundAttachmentFromBuffer` in `media/outbound-attachment.ts`\n- Regression tests in `message-action-params.test.ts` and `message-action-runner.media.test.ts`\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nCloses #90768\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\n- ClawSweeper review on #90768 (`clawsweeper:queueable-fix`, `clawsweeper:fix-shape-clear`, `clawsweeper:source-repro`)\n- Narrower than related outbound media issues `#20258` / `#50312` per reporter\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\n- Community report; ClawSweeper identified source-repro path and acceptance tests.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Buffer-only `message.send` attachments materialize to outbound media paths before channel dispatch; payloads above the default media byte cap are rejected before staging/dispatch.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local checkout on branch `fix/issue-90768-send-buffer-materialize`, Vitest on Windows host (`E:/Projects/skills/work/openclaw`).\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/outbound-attachment.test.ts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/outbound/message-action-params.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.media.test.ts -t \"buffer-only|oversized|materializ\" --reporter=verbose`\n  - `pnpm check:test-types`\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"vitest\": {\n    \"command\": \"run-vitest -t \\\"buffer-only|oversized|materializ\\\"\",\n    \"result\": \"Test Files 2 passed | 1 skipped (3); Tests 6 passed | 57 skipped (63)\",\n    \"passed\": [\n      \"materializes buffer-only send params into outbound media paths\",\n      \"rejects oversized buffer-only send params against the default media byte cap\",\n      \"skips send buffer materialization when an explicit media source is present\",\n      \"hydrates send actions through buffer materialization\",\n      \"materializes buffer-only send attachments into outbound media paths\",\n      \"rejects oversized buffer-only send attachments before channel dispatch\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"staging_proof\": {\n    \"input\": {\n      \"buffer\": \"YXJ0aWZhY3QgYnl0ZXM=\",\n      \"filename\": \"artifact.txt\",\n      \"contentType\": \"text/plain\"\n    },\n    \"observed\": {\n      \"args.media\": \"<staged outbound path under OpenClaw media store>\",\n      \"args.mediaUrl\": \"<same staged path>\",\n      \"args.mediaUrls\": [\"<same staged path>\"],\n      \"fs.readFile(stagedPath)\": \"artifact bytes\",\n      \"executeSendAction.mediaUrl\": \"<same staged path>\",\n      \"executeSendAction.mediaUrls\": [\"<same staged path>\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"byte_cap_proof\": {\n    \"input\": { \"bufferBytes\": \"MEDIA_MAX_BYTES + 1\" },\n    \"observed\": {\n      \"materializeSendBufferMediaParams\": \"rejects with /exceeds|limit/i\",\n      \"args.media\": \"undefined (not staged)\",\n      \"runMessageAction.executeSendAction\": \"not called\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"check:test-types\": \"exit 0\"\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Staged file at `sendResult.mediaUrl` / `args.media` contains `artifact bytes`; `executeSendAction` receives the same path in `mediaUrl` and `mediaUrls`. Oversized buffer-only sends throw before staging and never reach `executeSendAction`.\n- **What was not tested:** Live channel delivery on reporter's self-hosted runtime; all channel plugins end-to-end.\n- **Proof limitations:** Deterministic Vitest harness with mocked `executeSendAction`; proves staging, byte-cap enforcement, and send wiring (L1/L2), not end-to-end Telegram/Slack delivery (L3).\n- **Before evidence (optional):** `hydrateAttachmentParamsForAction` skipped `send`; `buildSendPayloadParts` only merged explicit media hints, so buffer-only sends lacked `mediaUrl` and failed `send requires text or media` or delivered without attachment. Initial draft used an unbounded `maxBytes` fallback; this revision enforces `MEDIA_MAX_BYTES` via `resolveSendBufferMaxBytes`.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/outbound-attachment.test.ts` → 2 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/outbound/message-action-params.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.media.test.ts -t \"buffer-only|oversized|materializ\"` → 6 passed\n- `pnpm check:test-types` → exit 0\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- `resolveOutboundAttachmentFromBuffer` stages outbound buffers with filename/content type.\n- `materializeSendBufferMediaParams` writes buffer-only send args to outbound media paths; skips when explicit media source exists; enforces `resolveSendBufferMaxBytes` (`resolveAttachmentMaxBytes` ?? `MEDIA_MAX_BYTES`).\n- `runMessageAction` send integration verifies `executeSendAction` receives staged `mediaUrl`/`mediaUrls`.\n- Oversized buffer-only send rejection at param materialization and before channel dispatch.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\n- Buffer-only `message.send` never converted `buffer` into a deliverable `mediaUrl` for the core send path.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\n- N/A — regression tests added.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\n- Staging buffer-only sends into the outbound media store when no explicit media path/URL was provided.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\n- Skips materialization when any explicit media source or structured attachment URL/path is already present; reuses existing `saveMediaBuffer` outbound subdir; enforces default `MEDIA_MAX_BYTES` cap via `resolveSendBufferMaxBytes` (no unbounded fallback).\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\n- Maintainer review; ClawSweeper re-review after byte-cap + oversized regression fixes.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\n- CI on fork PR; live channel L3 proof not available in this environment.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\n- ClawSweeper P1: replaced unbounded `maxBytes` fallback with `MEDIA_MAX_BYTES` via `resolveSendBufferMaxBytes`.\n- ClawSweeper P1: added L2 staging proof (staged path + `fs.readFile` content + `executeSendAction` wiring) in Vitest.\n- ClawSweeper P2: added oversized buffer-only send rejection tests at materialization and runner layers.\n",
